    "Listing 5.3 is a snippet of the C++ code used for this purpose.",
    "In this code, the execution time is highest when inputs fall within the range of 0.6 to 1, and lowest when inputs are between 0 and 0.3.",
    "This behavior mirrors that of a 6-DOF robot, where collisions are more likely to occur if the angles of two joints are large.",
    "By applying RL algorithms with the same reward function and configurations used in the 6-DOF case study, successfully identified input values leading to execution times exceeding 100,000 nanoseconds.",
